main event: A bally-length object was tracked by ground radar and visually observed for over 2 hours, traversing the sky and disappearing/reappearing at regular intervals.
interesting points: The object traversed the sky for 5 minutes at a time, then disappeared and reappeared about a minute later, repeating this pattern for 25 minutes.
The object would sometimes descend, then climb back up.
Radar operators were able to track the object.
The total duration of the observation was 2 hours and 50 minutes.
The conclusion on the report was 'Unknown', indicating the object could not be definitively identified.
photographs: no photographs present in the report
